  "text": "min . As seen in Table 1 min is defined in terms of the total energy E (cal) in the calorimeter, which in turn is dominated by the large deposits in the forward region, which came from the underlying event. More importantly, those contributions are more or less equally spread over the forward and backward region of the detector, leading to cancellations in the calculation of the corresponding longitudinal P z(cal) momentum component. As a result, the first term in (2.9) becomes completely dominated by the UE contributions [CITATION_1] .",
